laboratory_examinations.findings: The appendix is dilated up to 1.6 cm, fluid-filled, and demonstrates mucosal hyperemia with surrounding fat stranding, trace fluid, and fascial thickening. 2 appendicoliths are seen measuring up to 1.3 cm. Other findings include a 1.8 cm simple cyst in the upper pole of the left kidney and diverticulosis of the sigmoid colon without wall thickening and fat stranding.
